            </div>
            <div class="faq-item">
                <h3>How do you evaluate an AI stock?</h3>
                <p>Evaluating an AI stock involves looking at its revenue growth from AI products, forward P/E ratio, competitive positioning, and overall market capitalization. Companies with strong AI revenue streams and reasonable valuations are typically preferred.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="faq-item">
                <h3>Are small cap AI stocks a good investment?</h3>
                <p>Small and mid-cap AI stocks like SoundHound AI (SOUN) or BigBear.ai (BBAI) offer higher growth potential but come with significantly higher risk and volatility compared to established mega-cap tech giants.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="faq-item">
                <h3>What is the top AI company stock right now?</h3>
                <p>NVIDIA (NVDA) is widely considered the top AI company stock due to its dominance in providing the GPUs necessary for training and running large language models and other AI applications.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="faq-item">
                <h3>Why are AI stocks so volatile?</h3>
                <p>AI stocks are volatile because the technology is rapidly evolving, and valuations are often based on high future growth expectations. Any changes in earnings reports or technological breakthroughs can cause significant price swings.</p>
            </div>
        </section>
